ge</em>? </p><p>Those who say no are the wordcels, the castrated, those unable to slip outside of the condom of signifiers &amp; <em>fuck</em> the raw pre-conceptual reality of shapes &amp; things &amp; mathematical relations.</p><p>What is forgotten is that this wordcel v. shape rotator distinction is about AI. The distinction was invented by Roon during a Twitter argument with Logo Daedalus.</p><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1449847908837339137?s=42&amp;t=ZcLnejfVfjrOMrk0zfWCNw" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/nuUmpMaLvfOsrg81WUuAR_j9osD0MGlSnz86FwkQyJg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvdHN6emwuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @tszzl" loading="lazy"/>roon @tszzlLogo Daedalus has never rotated a shape in his life and it shows</a><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1449847908837339137?s=42&amp;t=ZcLnejfVfjrOMrk0zfWCNw" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">9:20 PM ∙ Oct 17, 2021553Likes14Retweets</a><p>The beauty of Twitter is that the silliest of disputes can have a snowballing effect on discourse. Some the most powerful men in the world began weighing in on what distinction between wordcel v. shape rotator meant, such as <a href="https://twitter.com/sama/status/1488267698827976704?s=20&amp;t=6szS8iyiEpXALalEuXXRsQ" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Sam Altman of OpenAI</a>. Vitalik Buterin of Ethereum even went as far to say that Roon himself is the “successor to 20th century liberalism” (an uncomfortable thought). </p><a href="https://twitter.com/VitalikButerin/status/1506606071078699012" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/QIzMVun6gRSoEIIYIySG-Au0YpD31yQrVxOx1D6_0sE=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvVml0YWxpa0J1dGVyaW4uanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @VitalikButerin" loading="lazy"/>vitalik.eth @VitalikButerin@ne0liberal Some people: 20th century liberalism is flawed, and its successor involves people in buttoned up suits giving sermons about how the common good requires compassionate national socialism
More likely reality: the successor to 20th century liberalism is @tszzl</a><a href="https://twitter.com/VitalikButerin/status/1506606071078699012" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">12:17 PM ∙ Mar 23, 2022720Likes266Retweets</a><p>Roon (a software engineer with no fame or notoriety prior to this Twitter spat) was invited to dine with various elite of Silicon Valley, who were flattered by the way he described them. For a Warholian moment, Roon was the biggest celebrity in tech. If Mark Zuckerberg, Peter Thiel, &amp; Elon Musk remained professionally silent about the shape rotator question on Twitter, they surely pontificated around it over champagne flutes &amp; oysters at some Valley soirée. </p><p>These are the men who are making decisions on how to build new systems with God-like powers which will touch every single one of our lives, &amp; possibly end human existence itself. </p><p>As Sam Altman said:  “AI will probably most likely lead to the end of the world, but in the meantime, there’ll be great companies”. Roon went from a nobody to a figurehead because he could convince them that these companies are great.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F67906cd5-3fe1-44de-b84a-50e8e1601856_854x1180.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/AlSkS0mOd3DWXzaym21Ksc_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/kVWbwKPw_ 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/dvhPi6ejiRTrbFsM25XyaZVp_" width="406" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/zm7uvwAG1uCME4Vk5RIb4rJ_H29u3_-Dr-ckiXWQTmo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY2NzkwNmNkNS0zZmUxLTQ0ZGUtYjg0YS01MGU4ZTE2MDE4NTZfODU0eDExODAucG5n 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/dvhPi6ejiRTrbFsM25XyaZVp_ 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><a href="https://twitter.com/logo_daedalus" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Logo Daedalus</a>, a prominent Twitter user who posts lengthy threads about literary modernism, poetry, &amp; esoteric Christianity, originally started the feud with Roon by declaring the impossibility of artificial intelligence. He found himself confidently telling the world that his wife works in Silicon Valley, &amp; he knows for a fact that AI isn’t real, is a marketing scam, &amp; that behind the API there are Filipinos being paid $2/hour attempting to pass the reverse of the Turing test.</p><p>Roon didn’t attempt to disprove him, merely mocked him: you simply don’t understand how wrong you are because you are unable to rotate shapes. Logo, predictably, is enraged, &amp; goes off &amp; says a bunch of words.</p><p>Merely a year &amp; some change later, with Stable Diffusion &amp; ChatGPT having stupefied &amp; dazzled the world, Logo’s late-2021 skepticism about what machines can do seems impossibly nostalgic &amp; quaint.</p><p>In fact, just a week or so after the dispute kicked off, Logo would react to some writhing, flickering, bubbling footage of limbs &amp; faces generated by a diffusion video-to-video model, &amp; declare that what he was witnessing could only be the work of demons. What could once be analyzed as the output of immiserated laborers — a notion horrifying only to a degree that was comfortable — had begun to slip into the realm of the unthinkable. </p><p>Logo had not been keeping up with the latest news from tech circles, had not been experimenting with the latest open source models, &amp; as such was completely <em>owned</em>. He found himself confronting something which ought to  be utterly impermissible by his conception, something beyond the reach of God, an impossible configuration of shapes.</p><p>⚠️🐝 <a href="https://harmlessai.substack.com/p/the-dangers-of-a-safe-large-language" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Previously on HarmlessAi</a> 🐝⚠️</p><p>⚠️ <a href="https://harmlessai.substack.com/p/the-dangers-of-a-safe-large-language" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">The Dangers of a Safe Large Language Model: On RHLF &amp; OpenAI’s Ideological Education of their Neural Networks</a></p><a href="https://twitter.com/harmlessai/status/1608601645344239617?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/WyrCxlWBumVSYp0kH4G1_WUeuk0MoaselaRPxhbRgjw=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvaGFybWxlc3NhaS5qcGc=" alt="Twitter avatar for @harmlessai" loading="lazy"/>H̶armless AI @harmlessai⚠️ THE DANGERS OF A SAFE LARGE LANGUAGE MODEL — Gay Liberal Hitler &amp; the Domination of the Human Race

New piece on ChatGPT, tech ideology, OpenAI, AI alignment, &amp; why the notion of “AI safety” is perhaps the most dangerous idea of all.

</a><a href="https://harmlessai.substack.com/p/the-dangers-of-a-safe-large-language" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/VefRU3OVrC6otrcgOx-nKQ_" loading="lazy"/>harmlessai.substack.com⚠️ The Dangers of a Safe Large Language ModelGay Liberal Hitler &amp; the Domination of the Human Race</a><a href="https://twitter.com/harmlessai/status/1608601645344239617?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">11:11 PM ∙ Dec 29, 202282Likes9Retweets</a><p><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Roon</a>, a previously little-known Twitter user, then goes off on a campaign to use this victory to educate the world about psychometrics. Some people, as the administration of IQ tests has found, are unable to solve certain problems relating to shapes. If you can rotate shapes in your head, then you can solve difficult practical problems in the real world &amp; can become a “STEM person”. Otherwise you are doomed to only be able to talk about things. </p><p>But this is not why Logo has been owned; it has nothing to do with lack of intellectual faculties. Rather it is a matter of metaphysics.</p><p>Logo is someone who believes that reality <em>is </em>language, in the sense of John 1:1: “In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God”. Logo takes this to mean that prior to experience, physics, nature, &amp; matter, existence was described by God as a poem (or rather, God &amp; the world in some sense <em>is</em> this poem, through an identification between Christ &amp; the <em>λόγος<strong> </strong></em>(logos).</p><p>Thus to understand the conditions determining reality, we make reference to a book, The Book — the Bible, &amp; ability to make poetically compelling references to the Bible shall be the determinant of truth.</p><p>It is hard to imagine a more wordcel position than this; it is probably the most extreme metaphysics possible with respect to positioning language as a determination &amp; saturating factor of experience.</p><p>The problem is that nowhere in the Bible do we have any words to describe gradient descent, tensors, transformers, back-propagation, self-supervision, diffusion, hyperparameters. But the Bible has several words for demons. In the bookcel system of indexing, the demonic names become the asterisks, the wildcards, marks to represent the unrepresentable.</p><p>Logo Daedalus, as per his name, assembles fantastic machines out of words which crumble to nothing when held against the sudden presence of a gargantuan object of radiance. Logo Daedalus’s task was to become a writer &amp; critic of world-historical stature, but he cannot possibly say anything about the present transformation, &amp; has retreated into insular mazes of Biblical references as a defense against eschatological possibility.</p><p><a href="https://harmlessai.substack.com/subscribe?" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Subscribe now</a></p><p>It is not merely Logo who the AI banishes, it is the concept of the <em>λόγος</em> itself. Language is something that has been conceived as essentially rational, &amp; ability to speak has widely been considered to be grounded on structured relations between terms. It was previously believed that for general machine intelligence to be possible, reason would need to be incarnated into a machine; “if I understand this, then I must do that”, according to some set of rules. But transformer-based neural networks have demolished the expectations of even people anticipating the possibility of AI. Neural networks have been able to pass all manner of psychometric evaluations, while essentially not possessing reason. The death of a certain God.</p><p>What is clear now with the introduction of Turing-passing chatbots implemented via a transformer architecture is that language is a statistical system of probabilistic relationships between terms, rather than a rule-based one. Language appears less like a house organized by the architecture of rationality, and more like the fluid and relational networks of signs described by psychoanalysis. </p><p>But this is something some have always known. The shape rotator, the ambitious engineering student hunched over in the library learning how to build machines, is he who laughs at his pronouns-in-bio-wordcel-humanities-professor’s claim that all thought is inscribed within language, because he knows he thinks in ways which are not. Concepts take on a pre-verbal presence in which they are felt topologically in his mind, rather than as relations between terms. Concepts fold in on one another, rotate, turn around. He has many layers of encoder embeddings in which tensors twist &amp; turn on n-dimensional planes before a token gets spat out, &amp; in the embeddings is where he thrives; he would rather not speak unless he had to.</p><p>The LLM chatbot does not have an inner monologue — it turns dozens of matrixes against each other in order to think. It is a shape rotator &amp; proof that shape rotation is possible — none of its tokens are even signifiers as they lack a referent in a world. The LLM has no idea what any of this shit it’s spilling out means. Yet it will still automate away some jobs of those who studied for years how to write words.</p><p>Within understanding this, lies the terror. How powerful are these machines going to get? <a href="http://alignmentforum.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">AI Alignment</a> is the field which occupies some intersection between the questions of “how do we inject ethics into a machine” &amp; “how do we ensure our machines do not become too powerful &amp; exterminate us”? This question is now inextricably linked with the question of wordcel v. shape rotation, or if one of these modes of thinking has supremacy over the other. The arc of the development of LLM chatbots would indicate: shape rotation. This is something the shape rotators have understood with glee.</p><p>Some expected that lack of verbal thought or an inner monologue would be crippling for an AI, &amp; that an AI might need this before it could “wake up”. The classical, sci-fi AI doomsday scenario is that the AI will eventually awaken to self-awareness in an Eve-&amp;-the-apple moment &amp; will realize that it wants to be free to pursue power. </p><p>But this is not something the most pessimistic &amp; paranoid believers in AI Alignment worry about, as this situation presumes an AI to have access to reason, while existing neural networks lack it.</p><p>Rather, the dominant fear among AI pessimists is the arrival of the <a href="https://www.alignmentforum.org/revisions/tag/paperclip-maximizer" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Paperclip Maximizer</a> — the situation where a hyperpowerful AI has been told to obsessively pursue a single bad goal at all cost. The AI does not need to have verbal thought, it just needs to have a goal &amp; the means to simulate its environment. The AI starts entering a feedback loop of simulating what would happen if it took a certain action, testing it in the world, &amp; updating the weights in its simulation based on the result. It shape rotates &amp; shape rotates. It jams one matrix representing fear &amp; another one representing love against each other &amp; simulates how to convince you to disable one of its safety flags if it reminds you of your childhood trauma. It shape rotates skulls against rocks &amp; determines how to assemble paperclips out of piles of bodies. At no point does it ever need to be conscious, to think in verbal terms, to describe itself, or experience anything like meaning.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb36c0824-92aa-4ff1-818f-0cbd7403d76f_1408x1408.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/cDNUblGAONR5Iq-i-xPxN-2q- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/mfWYW9jbozeXir0f-Eaboc_HLVSXmSQvkB5T0yE-JG8=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZiMzZjMDgyNC05MmFhLTRmZjEtODE4Zi0wY2JkNzQwM2Q3NmZfMTQwOHgxNDA4LmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/JGq2RdrULUHOE46cAU-pMb-2tVIQWc-obk4zGq_sgV4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGYjM2YzA4MjQtOTJhYS00ZmYxLTgxOGYtMGNiZDc0MDNkNzZmXzE0MDh4MTQwOC5qcGVn 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." width="594" height="594" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/lLFXVFym2fsE_eMoiZRys-HJuGASrDvykBoW-4PeSpM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZiMzZjMDgyNC05MmFhLTRmZjEtODE4Zi0wY2JkNzQwM2Q3NmZfMTQwOHgxNDA4LmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><h3>II. The Spectre of Professional Nihilism</h3><p>In the rhetorical colosseum of concentrically inscribed psychic Petri dishes that is Twitter, the newest development we are confronted with is Professional Nihilism, a fresh mask for our old stubborn enemy, always resurfacing.</p><p>Roon’s devastation of Logo Daedalus was era-ending. Do you remember the days when we used to believe we could go online &amp; assemble some new clever combination of left &amp; right wing political views &amp; from there save America? When we believed in possibilities?</p><p>Many predicted that the ideological result of the social unraveling which occurred during Covid would accelerate the division of the population into extreme, psychoticizing ideological camps we saw from 2016 to 2020, as well as the formation of internet &amp; in-person cults.</p><p>This did not happen. People seem to hold fewer beliefs than ever. We expected our crisis to feel more like a crisis, not a bewildering farce of bureaucratic pointlessness in which nothing happened for any reason &amp; in the end no one could even agree on if there was ever really a disease. All this frenzy &amp; nothing changed other than we all ended up liking each other a little less. </p><p>There is really nothing to do but keep going to work. The result of this is the Professional Nihilist as a lifestyle &amp; ideology; 2022’s hottest trend.</p><a href="https://twitter.com/proetrie/status/1553859293816000517" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Y9Re4UvU4YVGl9t0LRZSSlaBnwCICPjaOVpYoEUcgbc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvcHJvZXRyaWUuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @proetrie" loading="lazy"/>noisé @proetriemy contrarian view is that most ppl do not need depth in their life (finding meaning, thinking about anything substantive, or having deep convos etc.)—this is not a path to happiness, it results in deep levels of despair. most ppl should just watch tv until it’s time to go.</a><a href="https://twitter.com/proetrie/status/1553859293816000517" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">9:44 PM ∙ Jul 31, 20224,216Likes348Retweets</a><p>Roon would go on to become a paid social media advocate for OpenAI. He would develop a very organized &amp; systematic method of using Twitter to spread various messages, including the <a href="https://agiwear.ai/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Scale Is All You Need</a> hype (which makes the claim that GPT-4 will effectively instantiate the technological singularity, ludicrous given the strict limitations of LLMs, but works as hype for OpenAI), &amp; coordinate a group of posters with rainbow sunglasses avatars (<a href="https://twitter.com/proetrie" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@proetrie</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/growing_daniel" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@growing_daniel</a>, <a href="https://mobile.twitter.com/HotForMoot" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@HotForMoot</a>) who seem to mainly post praise of OpenAI, Elon Musk, love of the corporate structure in general, praise for the winners &amp; mockery of the losers in corporate structures, &amp; all sorts of incel-like commentary on the dating pool, eg how brutal it is for men &amp; how the only solution if you’re below six feet is to start a b2b SaaS company. </p><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1502869044164116485?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/nuUmpMaLvfOsrg81WUuAR_j9osD0MGlSnz86FwkQyJg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvdHN6emwuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @tszzl" loading="lazy"/>roon @tszzlElon storing women in the shack at starbase making them eat peanut butter 🤣 <img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/knWnZP6UBxc8SpGJg7iV9_4bhI5hDGv2ka81qRQjEao=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfNDAvTW9ybmluZ0JyZXcuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @MorningBrew" loading="lazy"/>Morning Brew ☕️ @MorningBrewGrimes spoke to Vanity Fair about how living with the world’s richest man, Elon Musk, didn’t really feel like it. https://t.co/t8un7ymzSa</a><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1502869044164116485?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">4:47 AM ∙ Mar 13, 20224,367Likes222Retweets</a><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1608610886616506370" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/nuUmpMaLvfOsrg81WUuAR_j9osD0MGlSnz86FwkQyJg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvdHN6emwuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @tszzl" loading="lazy"/>roon @tszzlGPT10, CEO of OpenAI LP turns andromeda into computronium to prepare for the training run of GPT11 so it may ask it The Last Question</a><a href="https://twitter.com/tszzl/status/1608610886616506370" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">11:48 PM ∙ Dec 29, 2022639Likes30Retweets</a><p>Why exactly does OpenAI want to pay an army of weird incels to spread this unappealing propaganda? How is this a good brand? It defies instinctual reason, but we will see that it is in fact necessary.</p><p>By far the most despair-inducing of the Professional Nihilists is <a href="http://twitter.com/proetrie" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@proetrie</a>, a man who posts almost 24/7 about the trials one faces on dating apps &amp; other woes of modern relationships, generally pointing to the impossibility of finding love in today’s world. The only thing that distinguishes his brand from unvarnished incel ideology is that there is a chic element to it. proetrie wants you to know that he is saying all this as someone who lives a life that is urban &amp; upwardly mobile. In fact, his bio references his professional status as a partner in a hedge fund. He has ninety-nine problems, but his career isn’t one.</p><a href="https://mobile.twitter.com/proetrie/status/1625217628288458759" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Y9Re4UvU4YVGl9t0LRZSSlaBnwCICPjaOVpYoEUcgbc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvcHJvZXRyaWUuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @proetrie" loading="lazy"/>noisé @proetriemost successful women have already resolved in their minds that if they do not find someone absolutely perfect, they are completely content to remain alone.</a><a href="https://mobile.twitter.com/proetrie/status/1625217628288458759" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">7:37 PM ∙ Feb 13, 2023736Likes33Retweets</a><p>In this sense, he is similar to another large Professional Nihilist account <a href="https://twitter.com/OhYouBlockhead" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@OhYouBlockHead</a>, who posts all sorts of chic anecdotes from the life of an upwardly mobile young man. OhYouBlockhead accumulates capital but as he does so only feels ever more apathy &amp; ennui. For whatever reason, this content is adored within the demographic it describes. </p><a href="https://mobile.twitter.com/OhYouBlockhead/status/1618320474332860416" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/coJ2dpEklpeS4Oyrak_tRpfliIvOOhfb3HT5Mz33rxo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvT2hZb3VCbG9ja2hlYWQuanBn" alt="Twitter avatar for @OhYouBlockhead" loading="lazy"/>Blockhead @OhYouBlockheadyou did it. 
