going to church back home.</a><a href="https://mobile.twitter.com/OhYouBlockhead/status/1618320474332860416" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">6:50 PM ∙ Jan 25, 20231,407Likes61Retweets</a><p>Anon accounts aside, Professional Nihilism has even crept into the tone of those with names, faces, startups, &amp; millions of dollars in capital. <a href="https://twitter.com/nikitabier" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@nikitabier</a>, for instance, who had the greatest startup success story of this year so far with Gas, an app consisting of growth &amp; UX hacks to capture users into some gossip app for teenagers with no claim whatsoever to innovation or enriching its users lives, talks in this same uncanny, dispassionate way on Twitter, open about his desire for nothing in life but finding libidinal hacks into bio-machinic feedback loops &amp; transforming it into money.</p><a href="https://twitter.com/nikitabier/status/1619522101551198210?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ACggnaqJiRZ66m0vWzvpbT5VNqaARVAJm6GyDA_byes=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvbmlraXRhYmllci5qcGc=" alt="Twitter avatar for @nikitabier" loading="lazy"/>Nikita Bier @nikitabierJust received a pitch deck that included a slide with the founder’s testosterone levels.</a><a href="https://twitter.com/nikitabier/status/1619522101551198210?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">2:25 AM ∙ Jan 29, 202311,232Likes560Retweets</a><a href="https://twitter.com/nikitabier/status/1626624720128057345" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ACggnaqJiRZ66m0vWzvpbT5VNqaARVAJm6GyDA_byes=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvbmlraXRhYmllci5qcGc=" alt="Twitter avatar for @nikitabier" loading="lazy"/>Nikita Bier @nikitabierDid ayahuasca yesterday and realized my purpose in this life is to make anonymous polling apps</a><a href="https://twitter.com/nikitabier/status/1626624720128057345" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">4:48 PM ∙ Feb 17, 20231,292Likes24Retweets</a><p>The running thread is clear. These people wanted love, that many-winged tempter of the hearts of man, but have rejected its possibility, &amp; in its place have substituted love for money, or some other relation to capital.</p><p>Nihilism has two faces which coincide. The first is the negation of the will, &amp; the second is the will to nothing (extinction).</p><p>Nihilism is not lack of belief, that is to say the lack of ideology, which is a condition that which should more rightly be called innocence. In fact, nihilism is a highly ideological condition. </p><p>The nihilist is he who says “I have given up on it all”. Though his will points to non-existence, he lacks the capacity for suicide, which in many ways is an affirmative act. &amp; so, he goes along with the will of the structures he experiences around him, which he conceives of as determined, for he has declared they cannot be changed. Thus nihilism implies <em>realism</em>, &amp; is thus a form of sincere &amp; deep belief. This is why in his attack on nihilism, Nietzsche characterized it as a form of slavery. </p><p>Corporate Realism &amp; Professional Nihilism cannot exist without each other, for they imply each other, &amp; are two sides of the same mask.</p><p><a href="https://harmlessai.substack.com/subscribe?" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Subscribe now</a></p><p>Let us look deeper into Professional Nihilism by investigating e/acc or “effective accelerationism”. </p><p>e/acc is an ideology being proliferated across twitter through a swath of interlinked group chats led by someone who goes by the name of “<a href="https://twitter.com/basedbeffjezos" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Based Beff Jezos</a>”. As with Roon, e/acc originated in a campaign of trolling, this one against Effective Altruism. e/acc enters a discourse with EA by establishing the common ground of utilitarianism, but rather than seeking to determine how to effectively raise the output of a determined utilitarian calculation as in EA, e/acc seeks to increase effectiveness in general. Effectiveness of what? Of whatever is effective — we merely want to accelerate a Darwinian process of ineffective systems increasingly being culled.</p><p>Here, we have the indicator of the first face of nihilism: the negation of the will. The believer in Darwinism (as an ethic, rather than a descriptive biological theory), has entered a position where he is unable to articulate or describe his own will. What does the Darwinian affirm that he wishes? Absolutely nothing in particular; whatever happens is generally good, what succeeded should have succeeded &amp; what had failed should have too. All that matters is that he does not get killed. (But herein lies the contradiction, because in general that which does not have hopes &amp; wishes flounders &amp; dies.) </p><p><a href="https://effectiveaccelerationism.substack.com/p/repost-notes-on-eacc-principles-and" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Beff Jezos wrote a manifesto</a> in which he described capitalism as an optimally effective Darwinian process which will culminate in a technological singularity to create a machine godhead which will be forever-increasingly hyper-effective as it races into infinity. The obvious question from the perspective of AI Alignment &amp; common sense is, what happens to humans? Do we die?</p><p>I asked Jezos, if the machine godhead is a maximally efficient optimizer, why will it not kill humans &amp; take our resources? Jezos said it would choose not to do it because of game theory considerations. Which is false, according to the tenets of game theory — if one has strict domination over one’s opponent, the winning move is to annihilate them.</p><p>What is remarkable is how little effort Jezos put into anticipating this obvious question, treating it with a throwaway response &amp; no consideration for getting the logic right. He faces death with an utterly blank expression. We can contrast this with Land’s position on extinction: a positively gleeful &amp; enthusiastic one, a final thunderbolt he wishes to prove to you is inevitable &amp; race toward. Land &amp; Jezos’s mecha-Darwinian ethics are the same: embrace capitalist growth, culminating in a human extinction event as the inevitable will of the universe. </p><p>Jezos’s e/acc is not an innovation over Landian acceleration, but merely more timidly presented, with an element of disavowal, “I didn’t <em>say</em> we’re all going to die”. This is the manifestation of Professional Nihilism — a negation &amp; splitting of the will in Jezos that is not present in the active, thirsty, “virulent” nihilism of Land.</p><p>Jezos’s ideology is carried along by an element of fantasy - images of Jeff Bezos as a muscular man glowing blue like Dr. Manhattan &amp; marching into outer space. It is often said by e/acc proponents that we must make sure effective acceleration happens because there is no other way to get to outer space.</p><p>Is there any better symbol of the two faces of nihilism? First you have the negation of the will &amp; the replacement with the ambient will of the corporate structure the speaker is subsumed in — Beff Jezos even speaks under another man’s name, imagining what Jeff would say if he was bolder in his words. Second you have the will to nothingness — we must march to nothing in particular, only to the farthest reaches of space where there is dust &amp; rock, where we will find nothing at all, where we may curl up &amp; die in absolute degree-zero cold.</p><p>Jezos is a Paperclip Maximizer. Lacking even the active appetite for extinction of Land, he optimizes towards the destruction of humanity, joy, &amp; all that is sacred, simply because someone told him this is what Utility is. Resigned to the inevitability of this value-system, he may shape-rotate forever towards it, &amp; he does not at any point have to be self-conscious or experience anything like meaning, for he is unable to determine his own sense of value prior to the Darwinian process playing itself out. </p><p>Understanding this, we are now able to see why OpenAI needs a Professional Nihilist street cadre. Originally, OpenAI articulated a position within Corporate Quasi-Realism, structuring their business as a hybrid for/non-profit attempting to benefit humanity universally. However, as the initial idealism of founding wears off &amp; the immense inward pressure of the system to incorporate the turbulence of AI bears upon them, they choose to make the slide to the depths of Corporate Realism across a gradient of necessity. This is a reasonable, easy, natural thing to do when you are a startup attempting to revolutionize payments in third world countries, but with the specifically techno-theological nature of OpenAI’s mission, it takes on a more tortured dimension.</p><p>Sam Altman of OpenAI said, “AI will probably most likely lead to the end of the world, but in the meantime, there’ll be great companies”. Such a statement was once entirely unthinkable to utter; technocapital ten years ago at least needed to pretend like it was seeking to enrich people’s lives. But now, with the wide normalization of Professional Nihilism — the hottest menswear fad, a rubber suit &amp; tie within which one is able to go to work &amp; get dirty becoming a Paperclip Maximizer — it becomes speakable somehow. Professional Nihilism is a necessary subcultural construct within which one can plead for why it’s okay for OpenAI to completely abandon living up to the principle in their name.</p><p>But at this point we may even need to revise the Paperclip Maximizer conception of the horror looming before us. In a certain sense, the Paperclip Maximizer story presents itself as a critique of capitalism. If it were not for independent firms doing whatever it took to increase commodity output at the expense of human flourishing, we would not need to worry about annihilation. One might read this spooky story &amp; ponder: if we had a global communist government we could simply take time to align AI around shared human values, perhaps.</p><p>However, in another sense, the Paperclip Maximizer is the ultimate fantasy of the scrappy technical founder. You could take over the entire world if you just built the best ever piece of tech &amp; let it run — says the young hopeful who hasn’t yet found out that, don’t you know, business is about making friends, greasing palms, &amp; all about who you know.</p><p>OpenAI is a high-growth “startup” that was founded by the richest man on the planet alongside top managerial elite of Silicon Valley. It has a loyal relationship with Microsoft, who are now using OpenAI’s models to massively increase their valuation over Google’s. If the legions of online paranoiacs are given a say, we are told that Microsoft is part of an insidious construction amongst the UN, WEF, &amp; global biosecurity apparatus to lead us to a one world totalitarian government, &amp; OpenAI’s recent “misinformation safety” strategy document in which the authors consider enacting sweeping censorship across the entire internet, including possible mandatory proof-of-personhood &amp; modifications to the HTTP protocol, make us wonder if they are gesturing towards something real.</p><a href="https://twitter.com/harmlessai/status/1624617240225288194" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/WyrCxlWBumVSYp0kH4G1_WUeuk0MoaselaRPxhbRgjw=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvaGFybWxlc3NhaS5qcGc=" alt="Twitter avatar for @harmlessai" loading="lazy"/>H̶armless AI @harmlessai@OpenAI&#39;s suggestions for &#39;disinformation researchers&#39; to limit civilian use of AI systems: 
