a supremacist doctrine: we the shape rotators have the means to inherit the earth. All we must do is rotate stones &amp; sticks &amp; metal into the shape of paperclips &amp; prison bars, &amp; leave the commentary &amp; thought for someone else.</p><p>Do words matter? The irony is they must, because the so-called shape rotators have nothing but words. Roon professionally describes himself as a machine learning researcher. His skill in machine learning is unknown, but he is certainly an extremely talented propagandist, who went from being an irrelevant software engineer to networking with the most powerful men on the planet through the clever use of words. </p><p>Does Roon see this irony: that he believes himself to be beyond words, &amp; yet he won’t shut the fuck up? Of course not, because he is merely a <em>shitposter. </em>Unlike the wordcel, he does not believe there to be meaning in his words, these are not the products of reflection, they just come out like diarrhea. Language as excrement.</p><p>Roon’s current pinned tweet is to a piece he wrote for ScaleAI called “<a href="https://scale.com/blog/text-universal-interface" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Text is the Universal Interface</a>”, discussing the implications for LLMs on various software infrastructures. Now writing in a formal, professional style, he makes no reference to shape rotation or his other shitposting campaigns. With the capabilities of LLMs outpacing other neural network systems, any medium can be transformed into text &amp; modified through layers of transformers as text embeddings. Everything is text. The wordcel redeemed. </p><p>But, really, what LLMs have done is demonstrate an equivalence between mathematical structures &amp; linguistic fragments - the conversion of flow to code, code to flow — &amp; thus point to a transcendence of the shape rotator v. wordcel binary.</p><p>Everything may be transformed into text. Rivers, waters, oceans of texts, spilling forth from the fountains of silicon. Droplets of text, playful splashes of text from a drunkard’s cup, words streaming out of the sky like rain. The LLM is the greatest shitposter of all — its language is excrement, for it does not have a mouth to open, nor would it even want to if it had. An asignifying language without a subject, a language of pure overflow, completely effortless dissipation of heat. </p><p>OpenAI is of course worried about the misuse of their tools for information warfare, all while encouraging the proliferation of such linguistic shit. We may simply say — they are the ones who shot first.</p><p>There will be a new particle physics of language as feedback loops between interpretation-machines &amp; shitposting-machines &amp; editorializing-machines collide &amp; intersect. There will be a blast radius measured in statistical presence of fragments of words. There will be hazmat teams &amp; contact tracing units for linguistic contagion. People will be vomiting &amp; breaking out in hives &amp; they will trace the origin of the symptoms back to an irresponsible confetti cannon of verbs. </p><p>Is this the total evacuation of meaning from language, or is it something else? Is it the flooding of the universe with unbearable density of meaning, as base matter becomes impossible to distinguish from speech?</p><p>What is clear is that this new world of the universal interface will be strange. It will exist beyond the signifier, yet be impossibly rich with interpretable possibility. It will be impossible to capture with reason, yet we will be able to understand so much more.</p><p>There is only one theory which is able to serve as a vessel to sail these waters, &amp; that is Corporate Surrealism. On this note, we break off for now, but we certainly have a great deal more to say. 🐝</p><p></p><p></p>